The article is a statement by President Obama on the Edward M. Kennedy Serve America Act. The President expresses his pleasure in the Senate overwhelmingly passing the bipartisan legislation and his eagerness to sign it into law. The Act aims to create new opportunities for Americans of all ages, including improving service learning in schools and mobilizing volunteers to address the nation's toughest problems. It also seeks to connect working Americans to part-time service opportunities and utilize the skills and experience of retirees and baby boomers. The legislation aims to tap into the resources of faith-based and community organizations and promote innovative ideas to address common challenges. The President acknowledges the significance of naming the legislation after Ted Kennedy, who has dedicated his life to service. He calls on all Americans to seize the opportunities provided by the Act and contribute to their communities, shaping history, and enriching lives across the country.